
Alternate Data Streams 

Alternate data stream (ADS) are a file attribute only found on NTFS file system 

in this system a file is built up from a couple of attribute, one of then is $Data, aka the data attribute. 
Looking at the regular data stream of a text file there is no mystry. it simply contain the text inside the text file .

this one is sometimes referred to as the unnamed data stream since the name string of this attribute is empty (""). So any data stream that has a name is considered as alternate 

to find the hidden file use : 
command in cmd shell : dir /R 

then to read the hidden file run 
more < Hidden_file_name 

  

